This stunning Browning A-bolt Medallion is manufactured in Japan by Miroku using premium walnut for the stock and the unmatched quality of Japanese steel for the remainder of the gun. This particular model had a very limited production run making this a collector's item as well as a gentleman hunter's ideal rifle. The Medallion boasts a muzzle break to aid in recoil control due to the lightweight frame of the rifle chambered in the extremely powerful .325 WSM cartridge which has had immense success in both North America and the African plains for larger more exotic game. Additionally, this rifle has brand new Leupold dovetail mounts and rings alongside a Burris Fullfield III 4.5X14-50mm optic with a paralax adjustment. This added bonus is backed completely by the Burris "No Questions Asked" lifetime warranty on the optic meaning that any issues or damage to the scope can be covered in full after a short drive to Greeley to their facilities! It is extremely rare to find this rifle in captivity let alone finding one with an optic at such a low price!
